3964	\begin{lemma}[The over-site of a topological space is equivalent to its subspace site]
3965	  \label{lem:overEquivalence_mathlib}
3966	  \lean{TopologicalSpace.Opens.overEquivalence}
3967	  \mathlibok
3968	  \textit{Provided by Mathlib.}
3969	  For a topological space \(T\) and an open \(U \subseteq T\), the over-category
3970	  \((\operatorname{Opens} T).\operatorname{over} U\) of opens contained in \(U\) is equivalent to the
3971	  category \(\operatorname{Opens} U\) of opens of the subspace \(U\).
